b'' b'could somebody please _email_ me some info on either what gif or iff' b'file formats are, or where i can get such info?' b'' b'well, gif stands for graphics interchange format and was put forth by' b'compuserve back in or so. it was to create a format that could be' b'read and displayed by any system. gif is limited to bit color but has' b'a built in compression scheme (lzw?).' b'' b'iff is not really a graphics format, but rather a standard way to package' b'images, sounds, animations, text, or whatever into one file. iff was' b'created by electronic arts, i do believe (i could be wrong), for the amiga.' b'it was quickly adopted as pretty much the standard file format for the amiga.' b'the most common image format for the iff package is an ilbm (interleaved' b'bitmap?) but many others exist. this format supports bit color images.' b'' b'information on both of these and many more are available via anonymous ftp at' b'zamenhof.cs.rice.edu in the directory /pub/graphics.formats' b'(taken from the faq for this news group.) b'' b'wayne rigby' 